10. Write a program that converts distances measured in kilometers to miles. One kilometer is approximately 0.62 miles.
--------
# File: 1.2-deliverables-question-10
# Made 12.13.18 by Ksenia Z
# A program that converts kilometers to miles.

def main():
	# Desc
	print("This program converts kilometers to miles")
	# User input
	km = eval(input("Enter a distance in km: "))
	# Conversion equation
	m = km * 0.62
	# Conclusion
	print (km,"kilometers is",m,"miles")
	# Exit prompt
	input("Press <Enter> to exit") 
main()
